overview: The user wanted to improve the overall aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, feeling it lacked visual appeal and personality. The
  assistant conducted a detailed review of the app's current styling, including
  global CSS, layout, and individual UI components. It identified several areas
  for improvement, such as the generic color palette, plain backgrounds, and
  basic form elements. The approach taken was to implement a new, calming
  sleep-themed design. This involved updating the color palette to use deeper
  indigo/purple tones with soft teal accents, enhancing the main questionnaire
  form with decorative background elements and a more engaging progress bar,
  redesigning the introduction section with feature cards and improved alerts,
  and polishing form field components like checkboxes, sliders, and radio groups
  for a more refined and inviting user experience.
